feat(cn105): wide-vane capability detection

Actively probe once whether the wide vane is a powered louver or a
manual adjuster, persist the verdict in NVS, and hide the wide-vane
control in the web UI when it is manual/unknown (Option A).

- New capability module (main/capability.{h,cpp}): 4-state detection
  (unknown/supported/unsupported/inconclusive), NVS persistence with
  algo-version gating, background detection task, and Auto/ForceShow/
  ForceHide override.
- One-shot probe primitive in the CN105 driver
  (beginWideVaneProbe/endWideVaneProbeRestore/abortWideVaneProbe +
  sendWideVaneOnce_) that suspends wide-vane enforcement so the unit's
  real echoed position is observed instead of the driver optimistic
  write-back. Aborts and reconciles to latest user intent on any
  external change.
- /api/capabilities GET+POST and caps block in /api/settings.
- Web UI: hide wide-vane row when unsupported; new "Wide vane" settings
  card with status, override select, warning, and Detect button.

Verified on both heads (192.168.1.151, 192.168.1.108): both have manual
louvers -> detected unsupported -> control hidden; override ForceShow
re-shows it; UI validators pass.

